{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D26TE5AfCUSgvbLk5tA4pE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the necessary information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the backend account decoder patterns.\n\n## Account Decoder Pattern Report\n\nI've explored the backend account decoder implementation across the RNG Utopia backend services. Here's the complete pattern for you to replicate:\n\n### 1. **Main Account Decoder Module** (`services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts`)\n\n**Core Concept**: Uses Anchor's `BorshAccountsCoder` with IDL JSON imports to eliminate hardcoded byte offsets. The decoder is instantiated once at module load and reused for all account decoding.\n\n**Setup Pattern**:\n```typescript\nimport anchor, { type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nconst { BorshAccountsCoder, BN } = anchor;\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL as coinflipIdl, LordofrngsIDL as lordIdl } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\n// Instantiate coders once at module load\nconst coinflipCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(coinflipIdl as Idl);\nconst lordCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(lordIdl as Idl);\n```\n\n**Type Conversion Helpers**:\n- `bnToBigInt()` - converts Anchor's BN type to native bigint\n- `roundPhaseToNumber()` - converts Rust enum variants (e.g., `{ Waiting: {} }`) to numeric values\n\n**Exported Interfaces** (camelCase, BigInt instead of BN):\n- `DecodedCoinflipMatch` - 15 fields including creator, opponent, server, entryAmount, phase, commitment (32-byte array), algorithmVer, targetSlot, resolveDeadline, resultHash (32-byte array), result, winner, createdAt, matchId (8-byte array), bump\n- `DecodedCoinflipConfig` - authority, treasury, paused, bump\n- `DecodedJackpotRound` (for Lord-of-RNGs) - matchId, server, phase, commitment, algorithmVer, entries (array of {player, amountLamports}), totalAmountLamports, distinctPlayers, createdAt, countdownStartedAt, countdownEndsAt, targetEntropySlot, resolveDeadline, resultHash, winningOffset, winningEntryIndex, winner, creator, bump\n- `DecodedLordConfig` - authority, treasury, paused, bump\n\n**Decode Functions**:\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCoinflipMatch(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipMatch {\n  const raw: any = coinflipCoder.decode(\"CoinflipMatch\", data);\n  return {\n    creator: raw.creator,\n    opponent: raw.opponent,\n    server: raw.server,\n    entryAmount: bnToBigInt(raw.entry_amount),\n    creatorSide: raw.creator_side,\n    phase: raw.phase,  // Note: already a number for Coinflip\n    commitment: raw.commitment,\n    algorithmVer: raw.algorithm_ver,\n    targetSlot: bnToBigInt(raw.target_slot),\n    resolveDeadline: bnToBigInt(raw.resolve_deadline),\n    resultHash: raw.result_hash,\n    result: raw.result,\n    winner: raw.winner,\n    createdAt: bnToBigInt(raw.created_at),\n    matchId: raw.match_id,\n    bump: raw.bump,\n  };\n}\n\nexport function decodeLordRound(data: Buffer): DecodedJackpotRound {\n  const raw: any = lordCoder.decode(\"JackpotRound\", data);\n  return {\n    matchId: raw.match_id,\n    server: raw.server,\n    phase: roundPhaseToNumber(raw.phase),  // Note: requires conversion for Lord\n    commitment: raw.commitment,\n    algorithmVer: raw.algorithm_ver,\n    entries: raw.entries.map((e: any) => ({\n      player: e.player,\n      amountLamports: bnToBigInt(e.amount_lamports),\n    })),\n    totalAmountLamports: bnToBigInt(raw.total_amount_lamports),\n    distinctPlayers: raw.distinct_players,\n    createdAt: bnToBigInt(raw.created_at),\n    countdownStartedAt: bnToBigInt(raw.countdown_started_at),\n    countdownEndsAt: bnToBigInt(raw.countdown_ends_at),\n    targetEntropySlot: bnToBigInt(raw.target_entropy_slot),\n    resolveDeadline: bnToBigInt(raw.resolve_deadline),\n    resultHash: raw.result_hash,\n    winningOffset: bnToBigInt(raw.winning_offset),\n    winningEntryIndex: raw.winning_entry_index,\n    winner: raw.winner,\n    creator: raw.creator,\n    bump: raw.bump,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n```typescript\n// For getProgramAccounts filters\nexport function coinflipMatchSize(): number {\n  return coinflipCoder.size(\"CoinflipMatch\");  // Returns 247 (8 disc + 239 data)\n}\n\nexport function lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): {\n  memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string };\n} {\n  return { memcmp: lordCoder.memcmp(\"JackpotRound\") };\n}\n\n// For integration tests — round-trip encode/decode\nexport async function encodeCoinflipMatch(fields: DecodedCoinflipMatch): Promise<Buffer> {\n  return coinflipCoder.encode(\"CoinflipMatch\", {\n    creator: fields.creator,\n    opponent: fields.opponent,\n    server: fields.server,\n    entry_amount: new BN(fields.entryAmount.toString()),\n    creator_side: fields.creatorSide,\n    phase: fields.phase,\n    commitment: fields.commitment,\n    algorithm_ver: fields.algorithmVer,\n    target_slot: new BN(fields.targetSlot.toString()),\n    resolve_deadline: new BN(fields.resolveDeadline.toString()),\n    result_hash: fields.resultHash,\n    result: fields.result,\n    winner: fields.winner,\n    created_at: new BN(fields.createdAt.toString()),\n    match_id: fields.matchId,\n    bump: fields.bump,\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **IDL Import Source** (`packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport ClosecallIDL from \"./closecall.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport LordofrngsIDL from \"./lordofrngs.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\nexport { ClosecallIDL, CoinflipIDL, LordofrngsIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\nIDL JSON files contain:\n- `address` - deployed program ID\n- `metadata` - name, version\n- `instructions` - array of `{ name: string, discriminator: number[], accounts[], args }` \n- `types` - array of `{ name: string, type: { kind: \"struct\", fields[] } }`\n\n### 3. **Usage Patterns**\n\n**In settle-tx.ts** (instruction building and result derivation):\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL as coinflipIdl, LordofrngsIDL as lordIdl } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport {\n  decodeCoinflipMatch,\n  decodeCoinflipConfig,\n  decodeLordRound,\n  decodeLordConfig,\n  type DecodedJackpotRound,\n} from \"./account-decoder.js\";\n\n// Extract discriminators from IDL for instruction encoding\nfunction getInstructionDiscriminator(\n  idl: { instructions: Array<{ name: string; discriminator: number[] }> },\n  instructionName: string,\n): Buffer {\n  const instruction = idl.instructions.find((entry) => entry.name === instructionName);\n  if (!instruction) {\n    throw new Error(`Instruction ${instructionName} not found in IDL`);\n  }\n  return Buffer.from(instruction.discriminator);\n}\n\nconst SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(coinflipIdl, \"settle\");\nconst CLAIM_PAYOUT_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(lordIdl, \"claim_payout\");\n\n// Usage in settle function\nconst matchAccountInfo = await connection.getAccountInfo(matchPubkey);\nconst match = decodeCoinflipMatch(Buffer.from(matchAccountInfo.data));\nconst { creator, opponent, creatorSide, entryAmount, algorithmVer: algoVer } = match;\n\n// Build instruction with discriminator\nfunction encodeSettleData(secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return Buffer.concat([SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR, secret]);\n}\n```\n\n**In settlement.ts** (polling and filtering):\n```typescript\nimport {\n  coinflipMatchSize,\n  decodeCoinflipMatch,\n  decodeLordRound,\n  lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter,\n} from \"./account-decoder.js\";\n\n// Filter by fixed size for Coinflip\nconst coinflipAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [{ dataSize: coinflipMatchSize() }],\n});\n\nfor (const { pubkey, account } of coinflipAccounts) {\n  try {\n    const match = decodeCoinflipMatch(Buffer.from(account.data));\n    if (match.phase !== PHASE_LOCKED_VALUE || !match.server.equals(serverKey)) continue;\n    // Process match...\n  } catch {\n    // Handle decode error (stale account from previous deploys)\n  }\n}\n\n// Filter by discriminator for Lord (variable-size accounts)\nconst lordAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter()],\n});\n\nfor (const { pubkey, account } of lordAccounts) {\n  try {\n    const round = decodeLordRound(Buffer.from(account.data));\n    if (round.phase !== LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE_VALUE || !round.server.equals(serverKey)) continue;\n    // Process round...\n  } catch {\n    // Handle decode error\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**In pda-watcher.ts** (WebSocket change detection):\n```typescript\nimport {\n  coinflipMatchSize,\n  decodeCoinflipMatch,\n  decodeLordRound,\n} from \"./account-decoder.js\";\n\nconst COINFLIP_MATCH_SIZE = coinflipMatchSize();\n\nconnection.onAccountChange(pubkey, async (accountInfo) => {\n  if (accountInfo.lamports === 0) {\n    // Account closed\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  const data = Buffer.from(accountInfo.data);\n  \n  // Determine game type by account size\n  if (data.length === COINFLIP_MATCH_SIZE) {\n    const match = decodeCoinflipMatch(data);\n    if (match.phase !== PHASE_LOCKED || !match.server.equals(serverKey)) return;\n    onJoinDetected(pda, match.targetSlot);\n  } else {\n    const round = decodeLordRound(data);\n    if (round.phase !== LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE || !round.server.equals(serverKey)) return;\n    onJoinDetected(pda, round.targetEntropySlot);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**In integration tests** (mock account setup):\n```typescript\nimport { encodeCoinflipMatch, encodeCoinflipConfig } from \"../worker/account-decoder.js\";\n\nasync function buildMatchAccountData(params: {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  entryAmount: bigint;\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  targetSlot: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  matchId: Buffer;\n}): Promise<Buffer> {\n  return encodeCoinflipMatch({\n    creator: params.creator,\n    opponent: params.opponent,\n    server: params.server,\n    entryAmount: params.entryAmount,\n    creatorSide: params.creatorSide,\n    phase: params.phase,\n    commitment: [...params.commitment],\n    algorithmVer: params.algorithmVer,\n    targetSlot: params.targetSlot,\n    resolveDeadline: params.resolveDeadline,\n    resultHash: new Array(32).fill(0),\n    result: 0,\n    winner: PublicKey.default,\n    createdAt: BigInt(Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)),\n    matchId: [...params.matchId],\n    bump: 0,\n  });\n}\n\nmockConn.setAccount(\n  configPda,\n  await buildConfigAccountData(treasuryKeypair.publicKey),\n  { owner: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID },\n);\n```\n\n### 4. **Key Design Principles**\n\n1. **Single Source of Truth**: IDL JSON is the canonical definition—no hardcoded byte offsets or field positions\n2. **Type Safety**: Rust's snake_case fields → TypeScript camelCase in exported interfaces\n3. **Big Numbers**: BN → bigint conversion for JavaScript arithmetic\n4. **Enum Handling**: Rust enums decode as `{ VariantName: {} }` objects; requires custom mapping (e.g., `roundPhaseToNumber`)\n5. **Discriminator Extraction**: Pull instruction discriminators from IDL at load time, not hardcoded\n6. **Error Resilience**: Decode errors logged but don't crash workers; undecodeable PDAs tracked to avoid retry spam\n7. **Account Differentiation**: Size-based filter for fixed accounts (Coinflip), discriminator-based for variable (Lord)\n\nThis pattern eliminates all manual struct layouts and provides compile-time guarantees that you're using the correct field names and types."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a946c590e421f24e6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 62983\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 85131</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7e08aab-e81c-466a-b6c2-35d333150199","uuid":"17dd16da-8db4-4242-ba11-9e07ac8f6ed9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the backend account decoder patterns in `services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts` within `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/`. Read the full file. Also check what IDL imports are used and how coinflip/lordofrngs decoders work. Also read `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` to understand how it imports and uses the decoders. Read any related files that show how BorshAccountsCoder is used. Report ALL the code so I can replicate the pattern.","agentId":"a946c590e421f24e6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the necessary information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the backend account decoder patterns.\n\n## Account Decoder Pattern Report\n\nI've explored the backend account decoder implementation across the RNG Utopia backend services. Here's the complete pattern for you to replicate:\n\n### 1. **Main Account Decoder Module** (`services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts`)\n\n**Core Concept**: Uses Anchor's `BorshAccountsCoder` with IDL JSON imports to eliminate hardcoded byte offsets. The decoder is instantiated once at module load and reused for all account decoding.\n\n**Setup Pattern**:\n```typescript\nimport anchor, { type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nconst { BorshAccountsCoder, BN } = anchor;\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL as coinflipIdl, LordofrngsIDL as lordIdl } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\n// Instantiate coders once at module load\nconst coinflipCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(coinflipIdl as Idl);\nconst lordCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(lordIdl as Idl);\n```\n\n**Type Conversion Helpers**:\n- `bnToBigInt()` - converts Anchor's BN type to native bigint\n- `roundPhaseToNumber()` - converts Rust enum variants (e.g., `{ Waiting: {} }`) to numeric values\n\n**Exported Interfaces** (camelCase, BigInt instead of BN):\n- `DecodedCoinflipMatch` - 15 fields including creator, opponent, server, entryAmount, phase, commitment (32-byte array), algorithmVer, targetSlot, resolveDeadline, resultHash (32-byte array), result, winner, createdAt, matchId (8-byte array), bump\n- `DecodedCoinflipConfig` - authority, treasury, paused, bump\n- `DecodedJackpotRound` (for Lord-of-RNGs) - matchId, server, phase, commitment, algorithmVer, entries (array of {player, amountLamports}), totalAmountLamports, distinctPlayers, createdAt, countdownStartedAt, countdownEndsAt, targetEntropySlot, resolveDeadline, resultHash, winningOffset, winningEntryIndex, winner, creator, bump\n- `DecodedLordConfig` - authority, treasury, paused, bump\n\n**Decode Functions**:\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCoinflipMatch(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipMatch {\n  const raw: any = coinflipCoder.decode(\"CoinflipMatch\", data);\n  return {\n    creator: raw.creator,\n    opponent: raw.opponent,\n    server: raw.server,\n    entryAmount: bnToBigInt(raw.entry_amount),\n    creatorSide: raw.creator_side,\n    phase: raw.phase,  // Note: already a number for Coinflip\n    commitment: raw.commitment,\n    algorithmVer: raw.algorithm_ver,\n    targetSlot: bnToBigInt(raw.target_slot),\n    resolveDeadline: bnToBigInt(raw.resolve_deadline),\n    resultHash: raw.result_hash,\n    result: raw.result,\n    winner: raw.winner,\n    createdAt: bnToBigInt(raw.created_at),\n    matchId: raw.match_id,\n    bump: raw.bump,\n  };\n}\n\nexport function decodeLordRound(data: Buffer): DecodedJackpotRound {\n  const raw: any = lordCoder.decode(\"JackpotRound\", data);\n  return {\n    matchId: raw.match_id,\n    server: raw.server,\n    phase: roundPhaseToNumber(raw.phase),  // Note: requires conversion for Lord\n    commitment: raw.commitment,\n    algorithmVer: raw.algorithm_ver,\n    entries: raw.entries.map((e: any) => ({\n      player: e.player,\n      amountLamports: bnToBigInt(e.amount_lamports),\n    })),\n    totalAmountLamports: bnToBigInt(raw.total_amount_lamports),\n    distinctPlayers: raw.distinct_players,\n    createdAt: bnToBigInt(raw.created_at),\n    countdownStartedAt: bnToBigInt(raw.countdown_started_at),\n    countdownEndsAt: bnToBigInt(raw.countdown_ends_at),\n    targetEntropySlot: bnToBigInt(raw.target_entropy_slot),\n    resolveDeadline: bnToBigInt(raw.resolve_deadline),\n    resultHash: raw.result_hash,\n    winningOffset: bnToBigInt(raw.winning_offset),\n    winningEntryIndex: raw.winning_entry_index,\n    winner: raw.winner,\n    creator: raw.creator,\n    bump: raw.bump,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n```typescript\n// For getProgramAccounts filters\nexport function coinflipMatchSize(): number {\n  return coinflipCoder.size(\"CoinflipMatch\");  // Returns 247 (8 disc + 239 data)\n}\n\nexport function lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): {\n  memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string };\n} {\n  return { memcmp: lordCoder.memcmp(\"JackpotRound\") };\n}\n\n// For integration tests — round-trip encode/decode\nexport async function encodeCoinflipMatch(fields: DecodedCoinflipMatch): Promise<Buffer> {\n  return coinflipCoder.encode(\"CoinflipMatch\", {\n    creator: fields.creator,\n    opponent: fields.opponent,\n    server: fields.server,\n    entry_amount: new BN(fields.entryAmount.toString()),\n    creator_side: fields.creatorSide,\n    phase: fields.phase,\n    commitment: fields.commitment,\n    algorithm_ver: fields.algorithmVer,\n    target_slot: new BN(fields.targetSlot.toString()),\n    resolve_deadline: new BN(fields.resolveDeadline.toString()),\n    result_hash: fields.resultHash,\n    result: fields.result,\n    winner: fields.winner,\n    created_at: new BN(fields.createdAt.toString()),\n    match_id: fields.matchId,\n    bump: fields.bump,\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **IDL Import Source** (`packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport ClosecallIDL from \"./closecall.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport LordofrngsIDL from \"./lordofrngs.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\nexport { ClosecallIDL, CoinflipIDL, LordofrngsIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\nIDL JSON files contain:\n- `address` - deployed program ID\n- `metadata` - name, version\n- `instructions` - array of `{ name: string, discriminator: number[], accounts[], args }` \n- `types` - array of `{ name: string, type: { kind: \"struct\", fields[] } }`\n\n### 3. **Usage Patterns**\n\n**In settle-tx.ts** (instruction building and result derivation):\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL as coinflipIdl, LordofrngsIDL as lordIdl } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport {\n  decodeCoinflipMatch,\n  decodeCoinflipConfig,\n  decodeLordRound,\n  decodeLordConfig,\n  type DecodedJackpotRound,\n} from \"./account-decoder.js\";\n\n// Extract discriminators from IDL for instruction encoding\nfunction getInstructionDiscriminator(\n  idl: { instructions: Array<{ name: string; discriminator: number[] }> },\n  instructionName: string,\n): Buffer {\n  const instruction = idl.instructions.find((entry) => entry.name === instructionName);\n  if (!instruction) {\n    throw new Error(`Instruction ${instructionName} not found in IDL`);\n  }\n  return Buffer.from(instruction.discriminator);\n}\n\nconst SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(coinflipIdl, \"settle\");\nconst CLAIM_PAYOUT_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(lordIdl, \"claim_payout\");\n\n// Usage in settle function\nconst matchAccountInfo = await connection.getAccountInfo(matchPubkey);\nconst match = decodeCoinflipMatch(Buffer.from(matchAccountInfo.data));\nconst { creator, opponent, creatorSide, entryAmount, algorithmVer: algoVer } = match;\n\n// Build instruction with discriminator\nfunction encodeSettleData(secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return Buffer.concat([SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR, secret]);\n}\n```\n\n**In settlement.ts** (polling and filtering):\n```typescript\nimport {\n  coinflipMatchSize,\n  decodeCoinflipMatch,\n  decodeLordRound,\n  lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter,\n} from \"./account-decoder.js\";\n\n// Filter by fixed size for Coinflip\nconst coinflipAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [{ dataSize: coinflipMatchSize() }],\n});\n\nfor (const { pubkey, account } of coinflipAccounts) {\n  try {\n    const match = decodeCoinflipMatch(Buffer.from(account.data));\n    if (match.phase !== PHASE_LOCKED_VALUE || !match.server.equals(serverKey)) continue;\n    // Process match...\n  } catch {\n    // Handle decode error (stale account from previous deploys)\n  }\n}\n\n// Filter by discriminator for Lord (variable-size accounts)\nconst lordAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter()],\n});\n\nfor (const { pubkey, account } of lordAccounts) {\n  try {\n    const round = decodeLordRound(Buffer.from(account.data));\n    if (round.phase !== LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE_VALUE || !round.server.equals(serverKey)) continue;\n    // Process round...\n  } catch {\n    // Handle decode error\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**In pda-watcher.ts** (WebSocket change detection):\n```typescript\nimport {\n  coinflipMatchSize,\n  decodeCoinflipMatch,\n  decodeLordRound,\n} from \"./account-decoder.js\";\n\nconst COINFLIP_MATCH_SIZE = coinflipMatchSize();\n\nconnection.onAccountChange(pubkey, async (accountInfo) => {\n  if (accountInfo.lamports === 0) {\n    // Account closed\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  const data = Buffer.from(accountInfo.data);\n  \n  // Determine game type by account size\n  if (data.length === COINFLIP_MATCH_SIZE) {\n    const match = decodeCoinflipMatch(data);\n    if (match.phase !== PHASE_LOCKED || !match.server.equals(serverKey)) return;\n    onJoinDetected(pda, match.targetSlot);\n  } else {\n    const round = decodeLordRound(data);\n    if (round.phase !== LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE || !round.server.equals(serverKey)) return;\n    onJoinDetected(pda, round.targetEntropySlot);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**In integration tests** (mock account setup):\n```typescript\nimport { encodeCoinflipMatch, encodeCoinflipConfig } from \"../worker/account-decoder.js\";\n\nasync function buildMatchAccountData(params: {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  entryAmount: bigint;\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  targetSlot: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  matchId: Buffer;\n}): Promise<Buffer> {\n  return encodeCoinflipMatch({\n    creator: params.creator,\n    opponent: params.opponent,\n    server: params.server,\n    entryAmount: params.entryAmount,\n    creatorSide: params.creatorSide,\n    phase: params.phase,\n    commitment: [...params.commitment],\n    algorithmVer: params.algorithmVer,\n    targetSlot: params.targetSlot,\n    resolveDeadline: params.resolveDeadline,\n    resultHash: new Array(32).fill(0),\n    result: 0,\n    winner: PublicKey.default,\n    createdAt: BigInt(Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)),\n    matchId: [...params.matchId],\n    bump: 0,\n  });\n}\n\nmockConn.setAccount(\n  configPda,\n  await buildConfigAccountData(treasuryKeypair.publicKey),\n  { owner: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID },\n);\n```\n\n### 4. **Key Design Principles**\n\n1. **Single Source of Truth**: IDL JSON is the canonical definition—no hardcoded byte offsets or field positions\n2. **Type Safety**: Rust's snake_case fields → TypeScript camelCase in exported interfaces\n3. **Big Numbers**: BN → bigint conversion for JavaScript arithmetic\n4. **Enum Handling**: Rust enums decode as `{ VariantName: {} }` objects; requires custom mapping (e.g., `roundPhaseToNumber`)\n5. **Discriminator Extraction**: Pull instruction discriminators from IDL at load time, not hardcoded\n6. **Error Resilience**: Decode errors logged but don't crash workers; undecodeable PDAs tracked to avoid retry spam\n7. **Account Differentiation**: Size-based filter for fixed accounts (Coinflip), discriminator-based for variable (Lord)\n\nThis pattern eliminates all manual struct layouts and provides compile-time guarantees that you're using the correct field names and types."}],"totalDurationMs":85131,"totalTokens":62983,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1968,"cache_read_input_tokens":57413,"output_tokens":3598,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1968},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
